Package alfdozen.es_2023_2sem_terca_teira_leipl_grupoa

Class ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule

java.lang.Object
alfdozen.es_2023_2sem_terca_teira_leipl_grupoa.ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
The ControllerLoadFileBeforeCreateSchedule class manages the GUI components and events in the loadFileBeforeCreateSchedule scene. The corresponding GUI is used to select a csv or json file in the local file system, remotely or from a webcal and import the file in the application. With the file imported it is possible to create a schedule.
Version:
1.0.0
Author:
alfdozen

    • getFile

      private void getFile()
      This method is called by the event of clicking on the getFileButton. It opens a file chooser dialog so the user can choose the csv or json file that is mean to be imported. After selecting the file, it is possible to import the file chosen.

    • dealWithText

      private void dealWithText()
      This method is called when something is typed in the input textfield existing in the remote and webcal options. After typing something, it is possible to import the file chosen.

    • importFile

      private void importFile()
      This method is called by the event of clicking on the importFileButton. It imports the file that has been previously chosen according to the local, remote or webcal option. After successfully import the file, it is possible go to the create schedule scene.

    • createSchedule

      private void createSchedule() throws IOException
      This method is called by the event of clicking on the createScheduleButton. It returns to the create schedule scene.
      Throws:
      IOException

    • returnHome

      private void returnHome()
      This method is called by the event of clicking on the cancelButton. It returns to the main scene.
